			<item>
				<title>htaas - UofT CTF 2025</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/posts/uoft_htaas/</link>
				<pubDate>Wed, 15 Jan 2025 19:58:53 +0100</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/uoft_htaas/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;While playing UofTCTF I solved hash table as a service (htaas).&#xA;We were given a simple heap menu, which lets us create, get and set hash table entries:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;1. New Hash Table&#xA;2. Set&#xA;3. Get&#xA;4. Exit&#xA;&amp;gt; &#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Upon inspecting the source, we spot some interesting things. There is an array that contains &lt;code&gt;hashTable&lt;/code&gt;s,&#xA;i.e. it contains the number of entries in the hash table and its start address:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;0x5c1e1caad040 &amp;lt;hashTables&amp;gt;:&#x9;0x0000000000000010&#x9;0x00005c1e4f4072a0&#xA;0x5c1e1caad050 &amp;lt;hashTables+16&amp;gt;:&#x9;0x0000000000000000&#x9;0x0000000000000000&#xA;...&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Each &lt;code&gt;hashTable&lt;/code&gt; consits of &lt;code&gt;n&lt;/code&gt; entries, which look like this:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>TLN - snakeCTF 2024</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tln_snake/</link>
				<pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2024 08:46:34 +0200</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tln_snake/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;This weekend I played snakeCTF for fun and managed to solve a few pwns. One of them was TLN.&#xA;The challenge code was pretty simple, introducing a classical OOB index vulnerability:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-c&#34; data-lang=&#34;c&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#79c0ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;OPT_SET&lt;/span&gt;:&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Index: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    index &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;get_int&lt;/span&gt;();&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Content: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;read_exact&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;(notes[index].content), &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;item_t&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    notes[index].content[&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;item_t&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As you can see, no bounds checks at all.&#xA;The &lt;code&gt;notes&lt;/code&gt; array consists of elements of &lt;code&gt;item_t&lt;/code&gt;, which is defined like the following:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-c&#34; data-lang=&#34;c&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;typedef&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; content[&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;];&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;item_t&lt;/span&gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To sum it up: we can write 7 bytes at a time relative to the starting address of &lt;code&gt;notes&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;The declaration of the array is what&amp;rsquo;s particulary interesting. The keyword &lt;code&gt;thread_local&lt;/code&gt; is used here:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>valorn&#39;t - PlaidCTF 2024</title>
				<link>http://localhost:1313/posts/valornt_plaid/</link>
				<pubDate>Tue, 23 Apr 2024 20:00:41 +0200</pubDate>
				<guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/valornt_plaid/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;I solved the easy pwn chall &amp;ldquo;valorn&amp;rsquo;t&amp;rdquo; during PlaidCTF while playing with Friendly Maltese Citizens.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As usual, the goal was to win the game and read the flag&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-c&#34; data-lang=&#34;c&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; ret &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;play_pew_pew_game&lt;/span&gt;();&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ret &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;read_flage&lt;/span&gt;();&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#x9;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In order to win, &lt;code&gt;is_cheater&lt;/code&gt; had to be set and the enemy team win-counter has to be &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
